				<DIV>First off, I agree that adding new races is the safest thing to do (of course, keep in mind that new races equals more memory to store more images in every single zone).&nbsp; If I had to choose a race, I would probably select orc or kobold.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>While new classes are probably out, if we were to add a new class, I would want to see a rune monk, which would be a wizard/enchanter/monk hybrid.&nbsp; This would be a silk wearing class that could cast multiple layers of runes of protection on themselves (like enchanters can, but better).&nbsp; The rune strength would be affected by their total hp (i.e. more hp = more powerful rune).&nbsp; They main mode of damage would be elemental fists (flame/ice/acid, etc) which is a self buff that increases their damage by doing a particular elemental type of damage when they successfully hit.&nbsp; You can add in some utility spells from wizard or enchanter to round out the class.</DIV>
				
